  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @tnir, thanks for your pull request! Is there a reason you prefer this being in the library, rather than in user land? v2 has been last released around two years ago, meaning that most people would already have migrated to this at the time v3 came out (if I'm not wrong). \r\n\r\nthere are more changes than just `query` to `q` between v2's `urlSync`, so I'm not sure if this is fully correct. IIRC @damcou made a stateMapping which complied to both versions here: https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-magento-2/blob/53dadcc2d21251cc493ed35f6206f555df60fd03/view/frontend/web/internals/common.js#L543\r\n\r\nWould love to hear your view on this!",
