  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@Haroenv Thanks. Yes, many users already migrated to v4 (or v3 at least). I love `q` rather than `query`, which is the default v2 behavior. While it supplies `query`, `singleIndex` is so handy. The introduced stateMapping `singleIndexQ` would supply `q` in a light way.\r\n\r\nWhy `q`? Google (search) and Twitter search have used `q` so many users are familiar with `q`. Some developers would prefer using `q` without any coding of their own `stateMapping` to achieve end-user preference and/or a shorter user-friendly URL.\r\n\r\nAs becoming fat is not my favorite, I would like to know how I can resolve this kind of preference 😄 ",
